  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Rapid-sequence intubation is routinely performed in critically ill patients. It is unclear&#xD;
      whether different sedative agents may influence short-term outcomes after intubation,&#xD;
      specially hemodynamic stability.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
